            "len": 1342,
            "post_value": "The work I find most energizing at Microsoft sits exactly at this intersection: I built and standardized cross-functional alignment workflows connecting Safety Engineering, ML Infra, and operational teams, defined risk frameworks and go/no-go criteria for tightly coupled workstreams, and led an internal AI agent build that cut planning cycle time by 39%. That pattern, coordinating research, safety, and infrastructure toward a shared deployment outcome, is precisely what this role is asking for. The scale just shifts from resilience programs to model alignment and production deployment, and that shift is one I am actively seeking.\n\nCharacter.AI specifically is compelling because the technical bet here is unusually concrete: taking powerful pretrained models and making them genuinely safe, engaging, and scalable for over 20 million monthly users is not a vague safety mandate, it is a product and engineering problem with real stakes. The breadth of the stack, post-training, RLHF, annotation pipelines, serving infrastructure, UXR, all moving in parallel toward the same release, is the kind of program complexity I want to be building operational patterns around. The fact that alignment and deployment are treated as one integrated effort rather than siloed concerns is exactly the environment where a TPM can do meaningful work."
          }
